From: AgenticBrowser <build@agentic-browser.dev>
Subject: [PATCH] Inject deterministic noise into the canvas rendering pipeline

Detection vector: Canvas fingerprinting draws hidden text/shapes to a
2D canvas, calls toDataURL() or getImageData(), and hashes the pixel
output. The hash is unique per GPU driver, font rasterizer, and
sub-pixel rendering engine. JS-level noise via getImageData patching
is detectable because the override changes the function's property
descriptor and can be detected via fn.toString() probes.

This patch injects per-seed deterministic noise directly into the
Skia canvas backend at the pixel write level, before any JS API
is invoked. The noise is invisible to property descriptor checks
because no JS API is overridden.

Surface: graphics-2d
Closes: canvas fingerprinting, TRANSPARENT_PIXEL

--- a/third_party/blink/renderer/platform/graphics/canvas_2d/canvas_rendering_context_2d.cc
+++ b/third_party/blink/renderer/platform/graphics/canvas_2d/canvas_rendering_context_2d.cc
@@ -XX,7 +XX,7 @@ void CanvasRenderingContext2D::DidDraw(const SkIRect& dirty_rect) {
+  // AgenticBrowser: inject deterministic pixel noise before the
+  // canvas snapshot is finalized. The seed is set per browser launch
+  // via the --ab-canvas-seed=<uint32> flag. Noise is applied to the
+  // backing store so it's present in both toDataURL and getImageData
+  // output without any JS-layer interception.
+  if (auto* recorder = GetOrCreateCanvas()->asRecordingCanvas()) {
+    ApplyCanvasNoise(recorder, dirty_rect);
+  }

--- a/third_party/blink/renderer/platform/graphics/BUILD.gn
+++ b/third_party/blink/renderer/platform/graphics/BUILD.gn
@@ -XX,7 +XX,7 @@ sources = [
+    "canvas_noise.cc",
+    "canvas_noise.h",
